liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Oh what was that Steve Smith?! Smith has just clipped the ball straight to Duckett at mid on! It's a dumb shot to play. Smith has had a bit of a word with Jonny Bairstow on his way off, which is wild considering how bad Bairstow has been all series, but it was a horrible shot and Smith must be fuming. He's out for 2.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: SMITH IS OUT!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: That is a horrible shot from Marnus! Was his head clouded by what had happened before, where he was given a life? He sweeps, sends the ball out to deep midwicket where Harry Brook makes a really good catch. He goes for 33, a bit of a waste from Marnus. England, out of nothing, gets a breakthrough.
